<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0"
	  xml:id="dds-submit">
        <refmeta>
            <refentrytitle>dds-submit</refentrytitle>
            <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
        </refmeta>
	<refnamediv>
		<refname>dds-submimt</refname>
		<refpurpose>submits and activates DDS agents </refpurpose>
		<refclass>UNIX/Linux/OSX</refclass>
	</refnamediv>
	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<cmdsynopsis>
			<command>dds-submit</command>
			 <group choice="opt">
			    <arg><option>-h, --help</option></arg>
				<arg><option>-v, --version</option></arg>
				<arg><option>-c, --config</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></arg>
			</group>
			<group choice="req">
				<group choice="opt">
					<arg><option>-t, --topo</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></arg>
					<arg><option>-r, --rms</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></arg>
					<arg><option>--ssh-rms-cfg</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></arg>
				</group>
				<arg><option>--activate</option></arg>
			</group>
		</cmdsynopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	<refsect1><title>Description</title>
		<para>The command is used to submit DDS agents to allocate resources for user tasks. Once enough agents are online the command can be used to activate the agents - i.e. distribute user tasks across agents and start them.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
	
	<refsect1>
		<title>Options</title>
		<variablelist>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-c, --config</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>TODO</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>-t, --topo</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Specify a topology file.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>--r, --rms</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Defines a destination resource management system. At the moment only the SSH plug-in is supported, therefore <replaceable>arg</replaceable> should be equal to: ssh</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>--ssh-rms-cfg</option> <replaceable>arg</replaceable></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Specify an SSH plug-in resource definition file.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><option>--activate</option></term>
				<listitem>
					<para>Request to activate agents, i.e. distribute and start user tasks.</para>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
		</variablelist>
	</refsect1>
	
</refentry>
